			<description><![CDATA[<p>
As a fast growing eCommerce company, we like to work hard and play hard, always striving to improve our business, our people, and the experience for our customers. We are currently seeking a highly motivated and dedicated replenishment manager, with the primary focus on driving sales and profits through innovative replenishment approaches, industry knowledge and technical expertise to ensure inventories are in line with the company&rsquo;s objectives.</p>
<p>
<br />
Job Responsibilities:<br />
&bull; Lead and optimize current and future replenishment processes to drive revenue<br />
&bull; Utilize tools to manage buying teams in forecasting and replenishment and product specific analytics<br />
&bull; Aggressively manage unproductive inventory, identify trends and develop recommendations to correct issues<br />
&bull; Create seasonal profiles and coordinate forecasts<br />
&bull; Analyze inventory levels and optimize return on investment of retail inventory across multiple product lines<br />
&bull; Demonstrate up-to-date expertise and apply this to the development, execution, and improvement of action plan</p>
<p>
<br />
Required Experience &amp; Skills:<br />
&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in supply chain management, industrial engineering or business administration<br />
&bull; 3-5 years previous business experience with direct experience in supply chain management<br />
&bull; Proficiency in Microsoft office, with advance excel skills required<br />
&bull; Motivated, proactive and highly organized with strong attention to detail<br />
&bull; Ability to multi task and prioritize<br />
&bull; Strong communication skills<br />
&bull; High analytic ability<br />
&bull; Must be flexible, adaptable and able to work in a fast paced independently or on a team<br />
&bull; Must possess entrepreneur spirit</p>
